HEADWORD: Monodelphia
<hw>Mon`o*del"phi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>mo`nos</grk> single + <grk>delfy`s</grk> the womb.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The group that includes all ordinary or
placental mammals; the Placentalia. See <er>Mammalia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
